cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper presents a modified neural network model capable of simulating Markov Chains, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the training of the network and ensuring statistical properties, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper demonstrates applications of the network in simulating non-deterministic outcomes, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
